00:39:02.194 --> 00:39:03.612
I'll break her limbs

00:39:03.695 --> 00:39:07.157
with her father's
and bury them upside-down!

00:39:21.088 --> 00:39:23.340
KIM SEOK-TAE

00:39:34.393 --> 00:39:35.644
Come on.

00:39:36.019 --> 00:39:37.980
This time, let's break your legs first

00:39:38.063 --> 00:39:39.356
before your head.

00:39:39.731 --> 00:39:42.317
There's no better way
to silence the evictees

00:39:42.401 --> 00:39:43.986
than taking them to court with this.

00:39:44.403 --> 00:39:46.571
No, this won't do. Pass me that one.

00:39:46.947 --> 00:39:49.199
- Sir...
- Hold him.

00:39:49.282 --> 00:39:51.118
- You already hit me last week!
- Stop moving.

00:39:51.201 --> 00:39:53.078
You already hit me last week!

00:39:53.161 --> 00:39:54.705
- We have to go again if you move.
- Sir!

00:39:54.788 --> 00:39:56.164
Let's just do it in one-go.

00:39:57.833 --> 00:39:59.251
I told you not to move!

00:39:59.334 --> 00:40:00.335
Alright.

00:40:02.254 --> 00:40:03.255
Is it broken?

00:40:13.306 --> 00:40:15.684
I knew you looked familiar.

00:40:15.767 --> 00:40:20.397
How many times did I break his limbs
and hit his head?

00:40:23.984 --> 00:40:27.738
I wondered
why that bitch kept coming at me

00:40:27.821 --> 00:40:29.448
as if her life depended on it.

00:40:30.532 --> 00:40:31.616
How inspiring.

00:40:32.284 --> 00:40:33.368
So damn inspiring.

00:40:43.086 --> 00:40:44.087
Hey, Byeon.

00:40:44.463 --> 00:40:47.382
Dad probably has some slush funds
at Jeongdaun, right?

00:40:48.508 --> 00:40:50.635
Yes, I think so.

00:40:51.094 --> 00:40:52.846
He wants to sacrifice me

00:40:52.929 --> 00:40:55.015
because he doesn't want anyone
to mess with that.

00:40:56.099 --> 00:40:59.978
I can't let anyone take that money.

00:41:01.021 --> 00:41:03.482
That'll all be mine one day.

00:41:05.025 --> 00:41:07.903
Fine. I'll take one for the team.

00:41:12.949 --> 00:41:14.117
Hey, Dad.

00:41:14.201 --> 00:41:16.787
Delay that arrest warrant by a week.

00:41:17.079 --> 00:41:18.080
What for?

00:41:18.455 --> 00:41:20.916
I have some urgent stuff to take care of
before I go.

00:41:20.999 --> 00:41:22.292
Don't worry.

00:41:22.834 --> 00:41:24.628
Whatever it is, you only have one week.

00:41:24.920 --> 00:41:26.046
Alright.

00:41:32.219 --> 00:41:33.804
- Hey, Byeon.
- Yes?

00:41:33.887 --> 00:41:35.180
Find someone.

00:41:37.140 --> 00:41:38.725
What for?

00:41:38.809 --> 00:41:43.647
Someone to send
Prosecutor Kim Jin-a far, far away.

00:41:45.899 --> 00:41:49.236
We've been ordered to indict Tae-sik
under detention.

00:41:49.319 --> 00:41:50.904
He's begun to cut his ties now.

00:41:50.987 --> 00:41:52.489
But in this life

00:41:52.572 --> 00:41:54.324
we have to get Yong-hyeon's funds, too.

00:41:54.407 --> 00:41:58.328
That's the only way
to strike Sin-jin and Gwang-to, too.

00:42:00.413 --> 00:42:02.374
It's because of Yong-hyeon's slush funds

00:42:02.457 --> 00:42:04.876
at Jeongdaun Savings.

00:42:06.086 --> 00:42:07.712
I guess you were right.

00:42:07.796 --> 00:42:10.423
They wouldn't have allowed me
to indict him otherwise.

00:42:10.507 --> 00:42:11.633
And as it turns out

00:42:12.425 --> 00:42:14.261
the Deputy Prosecutor General ordered it.

00:42:14.386 --> 00:42:15.720
After Mr. Eom joined Haenal

00:42:15.804 --> 00:42:19.141
the prosecution has been
without a Prosecutor General.

00:42:19.224 --> 00:42:21.935
That leaves the Deputy Prosecutor General
to take over.

00:42:22.018 --> 00:42:23.687
Yong-hyeon would've requested it

00:42:23.770 --> 00:42:26.857
and Sin-jin would've told
the Deputy Prosecutor General to do it.

00:42:27.941 --> 00:42:29.276
He's sacrificing Tae-sik

00:42:29.776 --> 00:42:32.487
to stop further investigations.

00:42:33.655 --> 00:42:35.407
I guess money matters more than his kid.

00:42:36.616 --> 00:42:38.785
But Tae-sik has 50 billion won
in slush funds.

00:42:38.869 --> 00:42:42.414
How much does his father have
if they can throw that away?

00:42:42.497 --> 00:42:43.957
Probably a few hundred billion won.

00:42:45.167 --> 00:42:46.626
500 billion won, to be exact.

00:42:47.752 --> 00:42:49.713
Including the funds at other banks

00:42:49.796 --> 00:42:52.382
paper companies, and international banks,
probably in the trillions.

00:42:55.135 --> 00:42:57.179
That means we're giving them
what they want

00:42:57.262 --> 00:42:58.889
by ending it at Tae-sik's arrest.

00:42:59.222 --> 00:43:00.557
We can grab Tae-sik

00:43:01.224 --> 00:43:02.726
and shake up the whole S Group.

00:43:04.060 --> 00:43:05.812
Tae-sik may be the start

00:43:05.896 --> 00:43:08.190
but we can get to Yong-hyeon and Sin-jin

00:43:08.523 --> 00:43:10.692
and send them all to jail.

00:43:10.775 --> 00:43:11.860
Let's do that.

00:43:11.943 --> 00:43:13.695
We might as well arrest them all.

00:43:14.613 --> 00:43:16.823
There's something I haven't told you guys.

00:43:18.283 --> 00:43:20.535
There's another garbage
we have to take out.

00:43:21.578 --> 00:43:24.289
I followed Nam-yong one day

00:43:24.372 --> 00:43:25.665
and that was the day

00:43:26.291 --> 00:43:28.001
I found

00:43:28.084 --> 00:43:30.462
the worst trash of them all.

00:43:31.755 --> 00:43:33.006
Who's that?

00:43:34.132 --> 00:43:36.176
The real big hand that moves Korea.

00:43:37.594 --> 00:43:39.095
The leader of the shadow government

00:43:40.096 --> 00:43:42.140
Park Gwang-to, the former President.

00:43:46.061 --> 00:43:48.480
You're all here!
Why are you standing outside?

00:43:48.563 --> 00:43:50.857
- You have to open it.
- Oh, right. It's my office.

00:43:52.150 --> 00:43:53.360
Park Gwang-to?

00:43:53.443 --> 00:43:54.653
Damn...

00:43:56.780 --> 00:43:59.574
You know, I voted for that guy.

00:43:59.658 --> 00:44:01.409
This is ridiculous. I feel so betrayed!

00:44:01.493 --> 00:44:02.494
Here, Han-young.

00:44:05.872 --> 00:44:07.290
- I'll take two.
- Okay.

00:44:10.502 --> 00:44:11.628
Hold on.

00:44:12.963 --> 00:44:14.714
Are you two the only ones here?

00:44:18.301 --> 00:44:20.720
You know I have to exhaust my knees
because of him, right?

00:44:21.721 --> 00:44:24.474
My wrists hurt with all the paperwork.
Being a judge is hard.

00:44:27.060 --> 00:44:29.980
Reporters have to deal with just as much.

00:44:30.063 --> 00:44:31.356
You should have some, then.

00:44:31.439 --> 00:44:32.440
Come here.

00:44:32.899 --> 00:44:34.651
Open that. I'll give this to Ms. Song.

00:44:34.734 --> 00:44:36.319
- Here's your water.
- Thank you.

00:44:36.403 --> 00:44:39.197
You think our joints are made of steel
because we're prosecutors?

00:44:41.074 --> 00:44:44.244
Cheol-woo,
you can be so inconsiderate sometimes.

00:44:44.786 --> 00:44:46.079
I was getting some for you.

00:44:53.503 --> 00:44:55.046
By the way

00:44:55.755 --> 00:44:57.507
you all know the To's Club, right?

00:44:57.924 --> 00:45:00.760
The club for people who love Gwang-to.

00:45:02.345 --> 00:45:04.848
They'll try to kill us
if they know what we're doing.

00:45:05.890 --> 00:45:08.560
Yeah, he's not an easy one to take on.

00:45:08.935 --> 00:45:10.020
Feel free to forget

00:45:10.478 --> 00:45:12.063
everything I just said.

00:45:12.439 --> 00:45:13.815
How can I?

00:45:14.232 --> 00:45:16.026
- It's so interesting.
- Why?

00:45:16.443 --> 00:45:19.612
You think I'll get scared and run away
because it's the former President?

00:45:19.696 --> 00:45:21.197
Is that why you didn't tell us?

00:45:21.281 --> 00:45:22.866
Who do you think I am?

00:45:22.949 --> 00:45:24.075
Hey.

00:45:24.159 --> 00:45:26.578
How can we forget what you just said?
We're not goldfish.

00:45:26.661 --> 00:45:27.787
Suojae is

00:45:28.371 --> 00:45:30.874
the real powerhouse that moves Korea.

00:45:31.416 --> 00:45:33.543
Everyone there is terrible.
Terribly powerful.

00:45:34.336 --> 00:45:35.879
So, stay out of it.

00:45:36.921 --> 00:45:38.048
You, too, Ms. Song.

00:45:38.131 --> 00:45:39.215
- What do you mean?
- What?

00:45:39.299 --> 00:45:40.383
My gosh!

00:45:41.217 --> 00:45:42.385
I'm Seok Jeong-ho.

00:45:42.844 --> 00:45:44.804
I'm the one who discovered Suojae.

00:45:44.888 --> 00:45:46.222
There's no way I'm stopping!

00:45:46.306 --> 00:45:47.974
How can I do that?

00:45:48.058 --> 00:45:50.060
And you're not even asking me
to stay out of it.

00:45:52.062 --> 00:45:53.563
You said we were a team.

00:45:55.732 --> 00:45:56.733
One team.

00:46:05.241 --> 00:46:06.368
Oh, gosh.

00:46:07.952 --> 00:46:09.496
What are you two doing?

00:46:12.707 --> 00:46:14.125
It was an accident.

00:46:19.839 --> 00:46:21.299
You're trying to get Tae-sik

00:46:23.676 --> 00:46:25.011
because of your father, right?

00:46:31.559 --> 00:46:32.977
You ran a background check on me?

00:46:34.187 --> 00:46:35.188
No.

00:46:36.272 --> 00:46:37.482
I just happened to find out.

00:46:55.083 --> 00:46:56.751
TESTIMONY

00:46:56.835 --> 00:46:58.336
CONFIDENTIAL

00:46:58.420 --> 00:47:00.839
TESTIMONY BY KIM SEOK-TAE

00:47:10.306 --> 00:47:12.976
I beat up the protesting evictees

00:47:13.435 --> 00:47:15.103
and cussed at them.

00:47:15.520 --> 00:47:16.855
Because Mr. Jang Tae-sik

00:47:16.938 --> 00:47:21.192
of S Construction told me to.

00:47:21.651 --> 00:47:23.278
Mr. Jang

00:47:24.112 --> 00:47:27.282
banged my head against the wall

00:47:27.991 --> 00:47:30.201
and broke my arms

00:47:30.660 --> 00:47:32.579
using a baseball bat.

00:47:33.204 --> 00:47:36.791
I lied to the judge

00:47:37.375 --> 00:47:40.962
saying the protesters hit me

00:47:41.045 --> 00:47:43.173
and left me with a head injury
and a broken arm.

00:47:43.798 --> 00:47:45.008
The judge concluded

00:47:45.508 --> 00:47:49.721
that the protester beat me up.

00:47:50.889 --> 00:47:52.682
Mr. Jang paid me

00:47:53.099 --> 00:47:56.603
a million won
and paid for my hospital bills.

00:47:57.312 --> 00:47:58.855
Mr. Jang told me

00:47:59.522 --> 00:48:03.651
he'd give me another chance to make money

00:48:03.735 --> 00:48:07.489
and told me to come again
once my bones were healed.

00:48:12.243 --> 00:48:14.120
Dad was a bad man.

00:48:17.916 --> 00:48:19.918
But he loved his daughter

00:48:21.503 --> 00:48:23.254
to his bones, literally.

00:48:24.088 --> 00:48:26.966
Jin-a, have some meat.

00:48:27.050 --> 00:48:28.718
It's so good.

00:48:31.012 --> 00:48:32.931
Whenever Dad came home, injured

00:48:33.014 --> 00:48:35.308
- we ate out.
- Do you have money for this?

00:48:35.892 --> 00:48:37.519
Of course, I do.

00:48:37.602 --> 00:48:38.603
You want to see it?

00:48:40.772 --> 00:48:41.856
Ta-da.

00:48:42.440 --> 00:48:43.942
Jin-a, here.

00:48:45.109 --> 00:48:47.028
This is your allowance.

00:48:47.111 --> 00:48:48.988
You don't have money, right? Here.

00:48:50.114 --> 00:48:52.659
On those days,
I'd get my overdue tutor fees

00:48:53.409 --> 00:48:54.869
and pocket money.

00:49:07.215 --> 00:49:10.051
You know, I dream of the day

00:49:10.510 --> 00:49:13.388
you put on a white blouse every morning

00:49:14.222 --> 00:49:17.475
to go to a real job.

00:49:19.269 --> 00:49:20.853
I hope you'll get to work late nights

00:49:21.229 --> 00:49:23.231
and go drinking with your colleagues, too.

00:49:24.315 --> 00:49:26.025
I hope you'll get to live

00:49:26.526 --> 00:49:30.238
like everyone else.

00:49:31.781 --> 00:49:33.116
Gosh, what am I even saying?

00:49:33.908 --> 00:49:34.993
Let's go.

00:49:45.545 --> 00:49:47.297
He lived in hell

00:49:49.215 --> 00:49:51.467
but I guess he wanted me to live
like everyone else.

00:49:56.848 --> 00:49:58.433
But he had no idea

00:50:01.686 --> 00:50:03.354
I also wanted a dad

00:50:04.856 --> 00:50:07.150
who would put on a white-collared shirt

00:50:08.443 --> 00:50:11.112
and go to work in the morning
and come home in the evening.

00:50:12.447 --> 00:50:14.407
He didn't know I wanted a normal dad, too.

00:50:19.704 --> 00:50:21.873
I studied like my life depended on it.

00:50:24.167 --> 00:50:26.377
To get far away from my embarrassing dad.

00:50:33.259 --> 00:50:35.011
But before I could even run away

00:50:35.678 --> 00:50:37.472
he fainted.

00:50:40.475 --> 00:50:43.102
He was doing everything Tae-sik wanted

00:50:43.811 --> 00:50:46.147
and his body gave in.

00:50:50.360 --> 00:50:52.904
I only realized when my dad fainted

00:50:55.948 --> 00:50:59.535
that it wasn't him
from whom I wanted to run from.

00:51:02.455 --> 00:51:04.957
Instead, it was my guilt
of having been raised

00:51:08.169 --> 00:51:09.962
through his broken bones and head.

00:51:31.234 --> 00:51:32.860
Where did you get this, anyway?

00:51:42.453 --> 00:51:46.040
The evictee your father framed was

00:51:47.750 --> 00:51:50.461
my father.

00:51:59.178 --> 00:52:00.221
What?

00:52:00.972 --> 00:52:02.098
You knew about it?

00:52:06.227 --> 00:52:08.312
When we went to the junkyard.

00:52:17.780 --> 00:52:18.781
Hello?

00:52:18.865 --> 00:52:20.032
Do you need help?

00:52:30.251 --> 00:52:33.671
I went there to apologize
on behalf of my dad.

00:52:45.683 --> 00:52:46.726
I see.

00:52:59.572 --> 00:53:00.865
The lead judge of the case was

00:53:00.948 --> 00:53:03.534
Justice Hwang Nam-yong,
who recently resigned

00:53:03.618 --> 00:53:05.870
and Sin-jin was the associate judge.

00:53:06.329 --> 00:53:07.330
What?

00:53:07.413 --> 00:53:11.125
That was why I made Nam-yong resign.

00:53:19.091 --> 00:53:21.344
Tae-sik made a fortune
through redevelopments

00:53:21.427 --> 00:53:23.638
but hurt many people in the process.

00:53:24.388 --> 00:53:26.849
My father and yours

00:53:26.933 --> 00:53:28.518
as well as all the evictees

00:53:28.601 --> 00:53:33.147
who lost their homes
due to the redevelopments are all victims.

00:53:43.699 --> 00:53:46.410
Where your donation leads to happiness.

00:53:46.494 --> 00:53:49.163
Seonjin Happiness Foundation is with you.

00:53:50.206 --> 00:53:51.207
What a good man he is.

00:53:51.290 --> 00:53:52.291
- Right?
- Right?

00:53:52.375 --> 00:53:53.543
We should donate, too.

00:53:56.128 --> 00:53:57.213
Cut! Okay.

00:53:57.296 --> 00:53:58.589
- All good?
- Yes.

00:53:59.006 --> 00:54:00.883
That was a bit awkward, wasn't it?

00:54:04.762 --> 00:54:07.139
What a handsome old man.

00:54:11.686 --> 00:54:15.022
Oh, my. He donated all his wealth?

00:54:16.691 --> 00:54:19.944
There are so many amazing people
in the world.

00:54:21.153 --> 00:54:22.238
My gosh.

00:54:22.321 --> 00:54:24.365
Please use the money to help
the students in need.

00:54:24.448 --> 00:54:27.577
Yes, we'll put the money to good use.

00:54:27.660 --> 00:54:28.786
- Thank you.
- Yes.

00:54:28.870 --> 00:54:30.162
Give him a round of applause.

00:54:30.955 --> 00:54:33.082
- Here.
- Let's take a photo.

00:54:33.165 --> 00:54:35.084
- Okay.
- Smile!

00:54:36.085 --> 00:54:38.754
One, two, three, cheese!

00:54:39.422 --> 00:54:41.132
SEONJIN HAPPINESS FOUNDATION

00:54:41.215 --> 00:54:43.801
CHAIRMAN KANG SUN-CHEOL

00:54:48.055 --> 00:54:50.057
Yes, Mr. President.

00:54:51.809 --> 00:54:53.060
That's right.

00:54:53.144 --> 00:54:55.980
The story of the old man donating
all his money from collecting scraps

00:54:56.063 --> 00:54:59.317
seems to have touched people
really deep in their hearts.

00:54:59.400 --> 00:55:01.819
As soon as the story got out

00:55:01.903 --> 00:55:03.404
we got an influx of new donors.

00:55:03.487 --> 00:55:06.282
Some idiots even made huge donations...

00:55:06.365 --> 00:55:09.952
Oh, no. I mean, some people even made
huge donations.

00:55:11.329 --> 00:55:13.039
Yes, I'll always be careful.

00:55:13.122 --> 00:55:15.374
Yes, Mr. President.

00:55:17.543 --> 00:55:19.837
Mr. Kang, I've booked a room
at the hostess bar.

00:55:23.507 --> 00:55:25.051
What? Why?

00:55:26.510 --> 00:55:28.054
In broad daylight?

00:55:28.137 --> 00:55:30.222
A hostess bar? Seriously?

00:55:30.306 --> 00:55:31.599
- Get on the floor.
- Yes, sir.

00:55:31.974 --> 00:55:33.100
You moron.

00:55:33.184 --> 00:55:35.144
- Wake up.
- Wake up!

00:55:35.561 --> 00:55:37.104
- Be on your toes.
- Be on your toes!

00:55:37.188 --> 00:55:38.272
Get up.

00:55:39.190 --> 00:55:40.691
- Turn around.
- Turning around!

00:55:40.775 --> 00:55:42.360
- At a 45-degree angle.
- At 45 degrees.

00:55:43.986 --> 00:55:46.280
Let's go!

00:55:46.530 --> 00:55:47.990
- Let's go!
- Go!

00:55:48.074 --> 00:55:50.034
- Let's go!
- Go!

00:55:50.117 --> 00:55:51.160
Come on!

00:55:51.994 --> 00:55:55.164
Press 2 to confirm
that you're Ms. Park Mal-rye.

00:55:57.208 --> 00:55:58.501
Confirmed.

00:56:00.920 --> 00:56:01.921
It's done now.

00:56:02.421 --> 00:56:05.299
Now, they'll withdraw 10,000 won
from your bank account

00:56:05.383 --> 00:56:06.801
on the 25th day of each month.

00:56:06.884 --> 00:56:08.928
Oh, wow! Perfect.

00:56:09.011 --> 00:56:11.389
It's so thoughtful of you to do this.

00:56:11.472 --> 00:56:12.974
I know you have it hard already.

00:56:13.057 --> 00:56:16.394
No, some even donate everything they have.

00:56:16.477 --> 00:56:17.853
This is nothing compared to them.

00:56:18.562 --> 00:56:20.314
Whenever I think about my Na-yeong

00:56:20.398 --> 00:56:24.568
I feel like I need to do more good things
for good karma.

00:56:27.196 --> 00:56:30.658
I know I shouldn't donate anything
with this mindset.

00:56:30.741 --> 00:56:32.410
Why not?

00:56:32.493 --> 00:56:34.036
It's for your granddaughter

00:56:34.120 --> 00:56:37.248
and other children in the country.

00:56:37.331 --> 00:56:38.541
Right?

00:56:40.001 --> 00:56:41.002
Honey

00:56:41.544 --> 00:56:43.129
it's all sorted now. Let's go home.

00:56:43.212 --> 00:56:44.463
- Okay.
- And here.

00:56:45.297 --> 00:56:48.592
They were selling huge sacks of chestnuts
at the market.

00:56:48.676 --> 00:56:49.719
It's chestnut season.

00:56:49.802 --> 00:56:51.929
My gosh, you always have something for me.

00:56:52.013 --> 00:56:53.889
I don't know how to thank you.

00:56:53.973 --> 00:56:56.392
It's not that much. No need to thank us.

00:56:56.475 --> 00:56:59.145
Thank you so much.

00:57:03.024 --> 00:57:04.859
Don't you have a date? It's the weekend.

00:57:10.823 --> 00:57:12.074
I'm meeting Jeong-ho later.

00:57:13.242 --> 00:57:15.911
Why are you meeting a guy?
You have a girlfriend.

00:57:17.538 --> 00:57:19.540
Did she break up with you already?

00:57:20.416 --> 00:57:22.126
We fed her two bowls of rice that day.

00:57:22.209 --> 00:57:24.712
If she broke up with you after that,
that's stealing!

00:57:24.795 --> 00:57:25.838
Han-young.

00:57:26.547 --> 00:57:28.299
- Han-young!
- What?

00:57:28.382 --> 00:57:29.508
No, right?

00:57:30.843 --> 00:57:31.969
I'll see her again.

00:57:33.220 --> 00:57:34.638
See?

00:57:37.266 --> 00:57:39.518
Han-young

00:57:41.145 --> 00:57:42.897
you know that thing?

00:57:42.980 --> 00:57:44.398
Not even the Chief Justice

00:57:44.482 --> 00:57:46.734
let alone a judge, can understand
what "that thing" is.

00:57:46.817 --> 00:57:48.152
Stop it!

00:57:49.570 --> 00:57:50.821
You know the organization

00:57:51.238 --> 00:57:53.324
former President Park advertises?

00:57:54.408 --> 00:57:57.286
The one that helps kids in need
and sick kids.

00:57:59.663 --> 00:58:01.123
The Seonjin Happiness Foundation?

00:58:01.207 --> 00:58:02.958
Yeah, that one.

00:58:04.085 --> 00:58:05.920
You know Ms. Park, who brings us scraps?

00:58:06.003 --> 00:58:09.840
She's donating 10,000 won per month now

00:58:09.924 --> 00:58:12.384
so her granddaughter has good karma.

00:58:12.468 --> 00:58:15.179
That's more than a whole cart
full of scraps.

00:58:15.262 --> 00:58:17.056
That's huge for her.

00:58:17.556 --> 00:58:18.974
That being said

00:58:19.058 --> 00:58:21.060
I also want to do something good

00:58:21.143 --> 00:58:23.479
for your good karma

00:58:23.562 --> 00:58:25.272
and make some donations.

00:58:25.606 --> 00:58:26.899
They're good people, right?

00:58:26.982 --> 00:58:28.901
How can you doubt the foundation?

00:58:29.443 --> 00:58:32.321
You think Mr. Park would agree
to advertise a corrupt foundation?

00:58:35.407 --> 00:58:38.285
I donate to a different organization

00:58:38.661 --> 00:58:41.539
so don't ever donate to that one, okay?

00:58:45.668 --> 00:58:46.710
Okay.

00:58:46.961 --> 00:58:48.003
Okay.

00:58:54.093 --> 00:58:55.970
This is a search and seizure.
Please comply.

00:58:56.053 --> 00:58:57.429
The Chairman of Seonjin was arrested

00:58:57.513 --> 00:59:00.641
for misappropriation of money
and breach of trust in the past life.

00:59:01.058 --> 00:59:03.435
There were rumors
that Gwang-to was behind this

00:59:03.519 --> 00:59:05.354
but people eventually forgot about it.

00:59:07.481 --> 00:59:08.732
What are you doing?

00:59:08.816 --> 00:59:10.442
Let go! Where are you taking me?

00:59:10.568 --> 00:59:11.569
Fine!

00:59:11.652 --> 00:59:13.070
Cover the table with newspapers.

00:59:15.906 --> 00:59:17.241
What's all this?

00:59:19.368 --> 00:59:20.744
That's so much.

00:59:23.289 --> 00:59:25.291
People at the market brought them.

00:59:25.374 --> 00:59:28.210
Mr. Seok exchanges the food at the store
with them.

00:59:28.836 --> 00:59:30.713
We get so much food

00:59:30.796 --> 00:59:33.757
that my grandma and I are getting chubby.

00:59:34.216 --> 00:59:36.177
Ms. Park looks even prettier
with some chub.

00:59:36.260 --> 00:59:38.721
Stop the chitchat
and go back to your homework.

00:59:38.804 --> 00:59:40.097
I'm already done.

00:59:40.181 --> 00:59:42.224
Don't talk back! Do your homework!

00:59:42.308 --> 00:59:43.475
Enjoy.

00:59:45.811 --> 00:59:47.771
Hey...

00:59:49.315 --> 00:59:51.942
I didn't know you had this side of you.

00:59:53.861 --> 00:59:55.487
Don't be too kind to your part-timers.

00:59:55.571 --> 00:59:57.323
Look at her, talking back to her boss.

00:59:57.406 --> 00:59:59.033
It's like she has no manners.

01:00:02.745 --> 01:00:04.580
- That's not it.
- Huh?

01:00:07.875 --> 01:00:09.960
- Han-young...
- She's thankful.

01:00:10.336 --> 01:00:13.464
She was smiling,
but the way she talked back...

01:00:14.089 --> 01:00:15.841
- You saw her.
- Alright, let's eat.

01:00:15.925 --> 01:00:18.344
Mr. Park, you may be slow,
but you can still eat, too.

01:00:19.637 --> 01:00:20.888
There's a high chance

01:00:20.971 --> 01:00:24.308
that the Seonjin Happiness Foundation is
Gwang-to's pool for his slush funds.

01:00:25.017 --> 01:00:26.894
Let's give Tae-sik's case more publicity

01:00:26.977 --> 01:00:28.395
and strike Gwang-to, too.

01:00:30.522 --> 01:00:31.732
That won't be easy.

01:00:33.025 --> 01:00:34.985
He's so popular
that he could still get elected

01:00:35.069 --> 01:00:36.695
if he were to run for presidency now.

01:00:37.279 --> 01:00:40.199
If we don't strike him properly,
he'll get all of us.

01:00:41.367 --> 01:00:43.327
And his supporters won't stay still.

01:00:44.536 --> 01:00:45.788
That's why we have to expose

01:00:46.580 --> 01:00:47.915
Gwang-to's ugly real self.

01:00:49.124 --> 01:00:50.376
Here's a question.

01:00:50.459 --> 01:00:53.545
How will Sin-jin react to us
attacking the Seonjin Happiness Foundation

01:00:53.796 --> 01:00:55.381
and getting Gwang-to?

01:00:58.342 --> 01:01:00.469
You said they were a team.

01:01:00.886 --> 01:01:04.014
He'd try to use the Judiciary
to protect Gwang-to.

01:01:04.807 --> 01:01:08.644
But if we shake things hard enough
for Gwang-to to fall from his treehouse

01:01:08.727 --> 01:01:11.397
Sin-jin will be tempted to do otherwise.

01:01:14.608 --> 01:01:18.320
Because he wants to become
the leader of Suojae.

01:01:20.572 --> 01:01:23.784
This threat for Gwang-to will fuel a fire
for betrayal.

01:01:32.209 --> 01:01:33.252
Oh.

01:01:33.961 --> 01:01:35.087
About Tae-sik.

01:01:36.255 --> 01:01:38.424
His arrest warrant has been delayed
by a week.

01:01:38.757 --> 01:01:39.758
Why?

01:01:40.217 --> 01:01:41.635
The higher-ups wouldn't tell us.

01:01:42.136 --> 01:01:44.054
We have to wait a week, no matter what.

01:01:44.138 --> 01:01:46.849
In the past life

01:01:46.932 --> 01:01:50.019
Tae-sik poisoned a CEO of an affiliate
to stage a suicide

01:01:50.894 --> 01:01:52.980
and tried to stage my suicide, too.

01:01:53.564 --> 01:01:55.190
Something is definitely up.

01:01:55.983 --> 01:01:59.361
Was there anything odd
during his emergency arrest?

01:02:00.904 --> 01:02:04.116
He denied all allegations
and talked like a snake, as always.

01:02:04.533 --> 01:02:05.743
Think carefully.

01:02:10.039 --> 01:02:12.207
He talked about living and being in hell.

01:02:13.751 --> 01:02:15.002
But that's all crap.

01:02:18.047 --> 01:02:19.048
Wait.

01:02:38.650 --> 01:02:39.735
What was that?

01:02:42.488 --> 01:02:45.949
FIND HAPPINESS
WITH SEONJIN HAPPINESS FOUNDATION

01:02:57.836 --> 01:03:00.255
I can't stop thinking about it.
I can't sleep.

01:03:47.636 --> 01:03:49.972
You definitely slept well last night.

01:03:50.055 --> 01:03:51.432
Look at that glow!

01:03:54.685 --> 01:03:55.978
No need to come here anymore.

01:03:56.061 --> 01:03:58.439
I'll weld my door shut
or sleep outside if I have to.

01:03:58.522 --> 01:04:00.524
I'll take care of myself
until we get Tae-sik.

01:04:02.317 --> 01:04:03.444
See you at work.

01:04:04.820 --> 01:04:06.196
Hey, Jin-a!

01:04:08.282 --> 01:04:09.575
Hey, here.

01:04:12.035 --> 01:04:15.122
Don't just tase anyone who annoys you.

01:04:15.205 --> 01:04:16.623
Don't shoot at anyone, okay?

01:04:18.792 --> 01:04:20.127
Who do you think I am?

01:04:20.419 --> 01:04:21.503
I don't need it.

01:04:21.587 --> 01:04:23.297
What? Don't make me sleep here again.

01:04:31.513 --> 01:04:32.723
Thanks, anyway.

01:04:33.515 --> 01:04:34.516
See you at work.

01:05:09.927 --> 01:05:11.512
Goodbye, you crazy bitch.

01:05:17.267 --> 01:05:18.268
No.

01:05:21.647 --> 01:05:25.275
THE JUDGE RETURNS

01:06:03.730 --> 01:06:06.024
Sin-jin wants to be the new leader there.

01:06:06.108 --> 01:06:08.193
I was going to get rid of them all

01:06:08.277 --> 01:06:09.861
once I became the leader of Suojae.

01:06:09.945 --> 01:06:11.697
To break it, I must trigger
a fracture from the inside.

01:06:11.905 --> 01:06:14.032
The target is
Park Gwang-to, the former President.

01:06:14.116 --> 01:06:16.577
Your ammo is corruption
in the Seonjin Happiness Foundation.

01:06:16.743 --> 01:06:19.663
We found fraudulent ledgers!
How can we not investigate it?

01:06:19.746 --> 01:06:22.332
You want to strike the Seonjin Foundation?
I can help you.

01:06:22.416 --> 01:06:23.458
What the hell are you doing?

01:06:23.542 --> 01:06:25.586
Someone said I was garbage.

01:06:26.837 --> 01:06:28.297
That crazy bastard!

01:06:28.380 --> 01:06:30.465
Didn't expect my chance to come so soon.

01:06:30.757 --> 01:06:31.967
Do whatever you want.

01:06:32.050 --> 01:06:33.093
Bang!

01:06:36.054 --> 01:06:38.056
Subtitles by: Minsun Kim